Removed Methods
Comparator<Optional<T>> emptiesFirst(Comparator<? super T>) Returns a comparator of Optional values which treats Optional.empty as less than all other values, and orders the rest using {@code valueComparator} on the contained value.
Comparator<Optional<T>> emptiesLast(Comparator<? super T>) Returns a comparator of Optional values which treats Optional.empty as greater than all other values, and orders the rest using {@code valueComparator} on the contained value.
(Collector<T, ?, List<T>>) greatest(int, Comparator<?, super, T>) Returns a {@code Collector} that returns the {@code k} greatest (relative to the specified {@code Comparator}) input elements, in descending order, as an unmodifiable {@code List}.
(Collector<T, ?, List<T>>) least(int, Comparator<?, super, T>) Returns a {@code Collector} that returns the {@code k} smallest (relative to the specified {@code Comparator}) input elements, in ascending order, as an unmodifiable {@code List}.
